While the Subgroups may benefit at lower {{arxiv_2209_07250_FO0045||FO}} values when CNPs with counts a bit further away from the predicted count are correctly classified as Synonyms, at higher {{arxiv_2209_07250_FO0046||FO}} the CNPs with very low counts are still mis-classified as Subgroups if they have a high semantic similarity to the representative CNP.